Quote: The second mode [of tin mining], or streaming, is much more primitive and easy. This may be termed `surface work', as it is generally carried on in moorland plains and valleys, in shallow pits of only a few feet in depth, and at but a small distance below the surface of the ground.
Notes: (Colenso Cornish Tin Mines)
